{
  "local_port": 52810,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What should I wear to prom?",
  "response": "Choosing the perfect outfit for prom is an exciting part of the experience! Whether you're aiming for classic elegance, modern trends, or something uniquely yours, here are some tips and ideas to help you decide what to wear to prom:\n\n## **For Everyone: General Tips**\n\n1. **Check the Dress Code:** Some proms have specific dress codes or themes. Make sure to review any guidelines provided by your school to ensure your outfit aligns with the expectations.\n\n2. **Comfort is Key:** You'll likely be dancing and moving around a lot, so choose something you feel comfortable in. Ensure your outfit allows you to sit, move, and dance without restrictions.\n\n3. **Plan Ahead:** Start planning your outfit early to allow ample time for alterations, fittings, or finding the perfect accessories.\n\n4. **Coordinate with Your Partner:** If you're attending with a date, coordinating outfits or color schemes can create a cohesive and harmonious look in photos.\n\n5. **Accessorize Wisely:** Accessories can elevate your outfit. Think about jewelry, belts, ties or bowties, shoes, and other complementing items that enhance your overall appearance without overwhelming it.\n\n6. **Consider the Venue and Weather:** Take into account where the prom will be held and the expected weather. For outdoor venues, consider layers or appropriate footwear. For warmer climates, lighter fabrics might be more comfortable.\n\n## **For Boys: Suits and Tuxedos**\n\n1. **Classic Tuxedo:**\n   - **Color:** Traditional black, navy, or charcoal.\n   - **Accessories:** Crisp white dress shirt, bow tie or necktie, cummerbund or waistcoat, formal shoes (like Oxfords or patent leather shoes).\n   - **Fit:** Ensure the tuxedo fits well\u2014consider getting it tailored for the best appearance.\n\n2. **Modern Suit:**\n   - **Colors:** While black is classic, other colors like midnight blue, deep gray, or even burgundy can make a statement.\n   - **Styles:** Slim-fit or double-breasted suits are trendy choices.\n   - **Accessories:** Tie or bowtie, pocket square, statement cufflinks, and matching belt and shoes.\n\n3. **Themed Attire:**\n   - If your prom has a theme (e.g., masquerade, vintage), incorporate elements that reflect the theme while maintaining formality.\n\n## **For Girls: Dresses and Gowns**\n\n1. **Long Gowns:**\n   - **Styles:** A-line, mermaid, ball gown, or sheath dresses.\n   - **Fabrics:** Satin, chiffon, lace, or tulle for an elegant look.\n   - **Colors:** Choose colors that complement your skin tone and reflect your personal style\u2014pastels, bold hues, metallics, or classic black.\n\n2. **Short Dresses:**\n   - **Styles:** Cocktail dresses, fit-and-flare, or elegant mini dresses.\n   - **Fabrics:** Silk, lace, or embellished materials for a chic appearance.\n   - **Colors:** Similar to long gowns, choose hues that resonate with you.\n\n3. **Two-Piece Sets:**\n   - Combines a stylish top with a matching skirt or separate components for a modern and versatile look.\n\n4. **Non-Traditional Looks:**\n   - Jumpsuits or tailored separates can be a fashionable alternative to dresses, offering comfort and style.\n\n## **For Non-Binary or Gender-Fluid Attire**\n\n1. **Tailored Suits:**\n   - Opt for well-fitted suits in your preferred colors and styles, possibly adding unique accessories that express your individuality.\n\n2. **Mix and Match:**\n   - Combine elements traditionally associated with different genders to create a personalized and creative ensemble.\n\n3. **Statement Pieces:**\n   - Incorporate bold accessories, unique fabrics, or unconventional styles that reflect your personality.\n\n4. **Versatile Dresses or Gowns:**\n   - Choose styles that align with your aesthetic, whether they're flowing, structured, or somewhere in between.\n\n## **Accessories and Final Touches**\n\n1. **Shoes:**\n   - Ensure they are comfortable enough to dance in. Men might wear polished dress shoes, while women have options ranging from heels to elegant flats.\n\n2. **Jewelry:**\n   - Subtle pieces like earrings, necklaces, bracelets, or cufflinks can complement your outfit without overshadowing it.\n\n3. **Hair and Makeup:**\n   - Style your hair in a way that complements your outfit, whether it's an updo, flowing waves, or a sleek look. For makeup, consider the formality of the event and aim for a polished appearance.\n\n4. **Bags and Clutches:**\n   - Women might opt for small clutches or elegant handbags to carry essentials without being cumbersome.\n\n5. **Outerwear:**\n   - Depending on the weather, you might need a stylish coat, shawl, or wrap to stay warm.\n\n## **Final Considerations**\n\n- **Personal Style:** Ultimately, choose an outfit that reflects who you are and makes you feel confident and beautiful.\n  \n- **Budget:** Set a budget for your prom attire and explore options within that range, including renting, buying second-hand, or seeking out sales.\n\n- **Petite vs. Tall:** Select styles that flatter your body type. For example, high heels can elongate the legs for shorter frames, while certain dress lengths can complement taller figures.\n\n- **Sustainability:** If you're environmentally conscious, consider eco-friendly fabrics or renting your outfit to reduce waste.\n\nRemember, prom is a memorable event, and the most important thing is to feel comfortable and confident in what you're wearing. Enjoy the planning process and have a fantastic time!",
